This problem can be solved using a hash map to count the frequency of each character in the string.
Then, sort the characters based on their frequencies.
The last character with the maximum frequency will be the last non-empty string.
We will iterate over the string from the end and keep adding the characters to the result string until all characters with maximum frequency are found.
